ğŸ‘‰ This keeps your JAR light, because nothing is inside src/main/resources.

â¸»

âœ… 2. Run Liquibase CLI from anywhere, but point it to your projectâ€™s changelog folder

Open PowerShell or CMD, then:

cd C:\Tools\liquibase-4.30.0\

Then run Liquibase with:

liquibase.bat ^
  --search-path=C:\Projects\my-spring-app\liquibase\changelog ^
  --changeLogFile=db.changelog-master.yaml ^
  update

This works even though Liquibase is in C:\Tools and your project is in C:\Projects.

â¸»

ğŸ”¥ 3. If you want, you can set LIQUIBASE_SEARCH_PATH permanently

PowerShell

